translated: Lindell, Henning Robert, director, civil engineer, Jönköping, b. 9/7/88 in Jönköping, son of factory owner Henning L. and Augusta Söderström. Married in 1930 to Ena Nordin. Children: Hans b. 1930, Lena b. 1936. Completed his Master's degree at Jönköping University in 1908, and studied at the Royal Institute of Technology (Mechanical Engineering) from 1909 to 1912. Worked as an engineer at A-B Baltic Separator in 1914, and at LindeWs Vågfabr. A-B in Jönköping from 1915 to 1918. Became the managing director of the latter company as well as Forserums Mek. Verkst. A-B in 1918. Became a member of the board of A-B Svenska Handelsbanken's branch office in Jönköping in 1929, and served as chairman from 1936. Became a member of the city council (H) in 1930, a member of the committee for revised legislation on measurements and weights in 1931, a member of the Swedish Mechanical Engineering Association's executive board in 1935, chairman of the general local valuation institute and the Jönköping city park board, and a member of the county labor board, the county probation board, and the Småland and Blekinge Chamber of Commerce's labor committee. Hobbies: tennis, golf. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa. Please note that the '\d\d m. partners name' means that the person married in the year 19xx.
